<br>
in response to the pet indifferent thing that would solve a TON of problems, and I THINK it would be a great, however again I doubt verant will do it.<br>
Verant seems to think that pets need to have some risk in using them, and would need to validate some kind of control over a pet, if it was indifferent mages would excercise zero to no control over their pet, and thats not what verant wants.  This would give us what we want about pet not changing targets, which verant has clearly shown they dont want us to have.  It would also mean that when our pet is feared, it causes no problems other then the pet losing melee for a few till they get back, so that invalidates much of the point of valiant companion.<br>
